Anyways, my personal feelings kind of turned into a sort of PSA. But the fact of the matter is that they are intensely connected and intertwined, and I know I’m not the only local party official who feels this way, probably more often than we would like or admit to.
Please turn your frustration into real, tangible action.
We are doing the best we can. But you sitting on your couch tweeting about how this candidate or that candidate is failing? Helps nothing.

When you complain that Democrats aren’t doing enough, it’s because you don’t see what happens behind the scenes on your local level. You don’t see HOW MUCH there is that needs to be done, and how few people and dollars there are to make it happen.

Your local party needs help getting out the vote locally. We need you DESPERATELY. We need the $27 you just gave to the National candidate so we can utilize the texting programs and advertising initiatives that are already out there.
National candidates don’t need you. They have the big donors. They have the countless volunteers at their disposal.
Constructive criticism is great, but it is NOTHING without action to back it up.
Long story short, the best way to help Democrats? Help your local party. If your local party is already BANGIN? Find another nearby county party that needs help.

Putting my time and energy and money into and stressing over something that ultimately nobody is helping with, or seems to give a shit about unless it is directly benefiting them? I’m kind of over it.
I am ready to give up on everything but myself and my family and let it all sort itself out.

I am tired of the expectation that I have to be the motivator and cheerleader in everything. I can’t drag out the enthusiasm and participation from people who are unwilling or too complacent to give it. Not anymore. I can barely drag it out of myself at this point.

But honestly I really just want to run away and hide. Live alone in a cave for a few weeks and let people figure out their own shit and how to make it all work without my constant helping hand or guidance.
And it is my fault they see me this way, because I constantly overextend myself and push myself to do things exactly right.
I’m tired of everyone’s expectation that I do all of everything and do it perfectly without fail.
I’m just kind of sick of everything, tbh.
